COURSES.name: First Year Introduction: Biology at UF
COURSES.description: Introduces the field of biology and the academic resources specific to this discipline at UF. Discussions of the nature and practice of scientific research, laboratory safety, advising and career resources for biologists. Developments in the instructor's area of expertise are used to illustrate key subjects. (S-U)
COURSES.prerequisites: Credits: 1; Prereq: biology, botany, zoology or exploring science and engineering majors only.

COURSES.name: Biological Sciences
COURSES.description: A comprehensive introduction to living systems, including the scientific basis of biology, cell structure and function, genetic mechanisms, animal and plant anatomy and physiology, and ecology and evolutionary processes. Recommended for students not majoring in the natural sciences. (B)

COURSES.name: Laboratory in Biological Sciences
COURSES.description: A laboratory for students who need experience in a nonprofessionally oriented laboratory or for those who need laboratory experience to satisfy requirements for graduation. (B)

COURSES.name: Integrated Principles of Biology 1
COURSES.description: General Biology Core: the first of a two-semester sequence that prepares students for advanced biological sciences courses and allied fields. Studies the origin of life systems; of biological molecules and organization of living things at the subcellular, cellular and organismic levels; and of the activities of living forms in obtaining and utilizing energy and materials in growth, maintenance and reproduction. (B)

COURSES.name: Integrated Principles of Biology 2
COURSES.description: General Biology Core: the second of a two-semester sequence that prepares students for advanced biological sciences courses and allied fields. Examination in living things of the principles of information storage, transmission and utilization at the cell, organism and population levels; of the mechanisms of evolutionary change in the diversification of living things and their life styles; of population growth and regulation; and of energy flow and biogeochemical cycling in the biosphere. (B)
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: BSC 2010 or the equivalent. Degree-seeking students only.

COURSES.name: Integrated Principles of Biology Laboratory 2
COURSES.description: Laboratory experiments designed to accompany BSC 2011. Students should register for BSC 2011 and 2011L concurrently. (B)
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: Degree-seeking students only. Coreq: BSC 2011 or the equivalent.

COURSES.name: Global Change Ecology and Sustainability
COURSES.description: Examines key issues in sustainability and global environmental change from an ecological perspective. Major themes include impacts of climate change on terrestrial ecological communities; feedback between the terrestrial biosphere and the atmosphere; and implications of climate change for the sustainability of natural and managed ecosystems. (B)

COURSES.name: Human Physiology
COURSES.description: The functioning of human tissues, organs and organ systems, emphasizing the physical, chemical and mechanistic bases of normal physiology and the integrated function of the human body. Also introduces pathophysiological changes associated with human diseases.
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: CHM 1031, CHM 2046, or CHM 2047 and BSC 2011.

COURSES.name: Entering Research in Biology
COURSES.description: A seminar course to complement a students mentored research experience. Must be taken concurrently with research credits. Students meet weekly to share their research experiences and to get feedback on the progress of their research projects.
COURSES.prerequisites: Coreq: BSC 4910 or BOT 4905 or ZOO 4905 or IDH 4912

sections.note: PLEASE CONTACT ANDREA AT andrealsmith@ufl.edu for registration

COURSES.name: Individual Mentored Research in Biology
COURSES.description: Qualified students work with a supervising instructor on a research project in biology.
COURSES.prerequisites: Credits: 1 to 3; Prereq: BSC 2010, BSC 2010L, BSC 2011 and BSC 2011L with minimum grades of C; Coreq: BSC 3911.

sections.note: PLEASE CONTACT ANDREA AT andrealsmith@ufl.edu for registration

COURSES.name: Advanced Mentored Research in Biology
COURSES.description: Advanced students work with a supervising instructor on a research project in biology. May be repeated for full credit.
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: BSC 3911 and BSC 4910 with minimum grades of C.

sections.note: PLEASE CONTACT ANDREA AT andrealsmith@ufl.edu for registration

COURSES.name: Critical Analysis of Biological Research
COURSES.description: Critical analysis of current life sciences research through online discussions of research seminars and peer reviewed scientific publications.
COURSES.prerequisites: Credits: 2. Prereq: senior standing in biology, botany or zoology.

COURSES.name: Cross-Disciplinary Laboratory 1
COURSES.description: First course in a two-semester inquiry-based laboratory focusing on major themes and concepts in biology, chemistry and physics with an emphasis on their integrated applications in modern, quantitative research. Satisfies course requirements for BSC 2010L, CHM 2045L and PHY 2053L.
COURSES.prerequisites: Prereq: high school algebra or equivalent.

COURSES.name: Cross-Disciplinary Laboratory 2
COURSES.description: Second course in a two-semester inquiry-based laboratory focusing on major themes and concepts in biology, chemistry and physics with an emphasis on their integrated applications in modern, quantitative research. Satisfies course requirements for BSC 2011L, CHM 2046L and PHY 2054L.
